article.description: — Zach Nutall had 18 points as Sam Houston defeated Lamar 77-71 on Monday night.
article.headline: Nutall, Powers lead Sam Houston St. over Lamar 77-71
article.linkText: Nutall, Powers lead Sam Houston St. over Lamar 77-71
article.story: BEAUMONT, Texas -- — Zach Nutall had 18 points as Sam Houston defeated Lamar 77-71 on Monday night. Donte Powers added 17 points for the Bearkats, while Demarkus Lampley chipped in 16. Bryce Monroe had 12 points for Sam Houston (17-6, 11-1 Southland Conference), which earned its fourth consecutive victory. Davion Buster had 19 points for the Cardinals (4-17, 3-10), who have now lost six consecutive games. Ellis Jefferson added 17 points and seven rebounds. Kasen Harrison had 15 points. Avery Sullivan tied a career high with 16 rebounds plus 8 points. The Bearkats improve to 2-0 against the Cardinals for the season. Sam Houston defeated Lamar 96-71 on Jan. 13. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
